post: {'type': 'con', 'text': "Several 'great' artists have died from an overdose on drugs and thus actually causing negative contributions to human culture as the world is deprived of their 'artwork'."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If an individual is already addicted, that would indicate they already have regular access to the drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, the potency of available alcoholic drinks grew significantly \\([pg. 3](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This limits what we know about these compounds as well as to what length we are able to develop treatments for those struggling with addiction \\(physical and mental\\) as well as treatment for acute toxicity.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow access to drugs to be graded based on risks taking them, meaning more addictive and harmful drugs could be made less available and desirable by taxing them accordingly.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The first [anti-cocaine laws](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/brief-history-drug-war) in the early 1900s were directed at black men in the South.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the war on drugs were won, these jobs would also be lost.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some drugs - hypnotics and barbiturates in particular - are used maliciously as date-rape drugs. Control of these drugs may be preventing rapes from occurring. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is little medical discrimination for those who use legal harmful substances such as alcohol or tobacco.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Rational discussion of the costs and benefits of smoking tobacco and negative ads led a lot of people to decide it isn't worth doing. All without prohibiting it."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs being legalized would allow the injured victims \\(or their heirs\\) of fraudulently/irresponsibly cut/marketed drugs to legally and publicly sue the manufacturer/distributor for damages, thereby using market pressures to better assure product/service quality/safety. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Governments manipulate citizens by spreading biased information about drugs and thereby interfering with their choices. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legal sellers will be highly scrutinized and won't want to risk losing their license. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of a drug means more education and informing for children in this matter. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The cigarette industry suppressed research that demonstrated the carcinogenicity of cigarettes \\([pg. 2](https://www.who.int/tobacco/media/en/TobaccoExplained.pdf)\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help drive down the profits of drug cartels since people could get their drugs from legal reliable sources. Hence it may force the cartels to offer a purer product or less expensive to remain competitive. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Even if criminals are able to offer drugs at lower prices, people would turn to legal drugs because they would not risk prison and they would be sure of the quality of what they're buying. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a tautological argument, presupposing that prohibiting drugs is morally right.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'While some might overestimate the revenue, there still will be revenue. If it is 1/2 or 1/3 of those naive estimates, it is still revenue, and it still increases the government coffers.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In some instances, drug use has increased following legalisation. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A family member may stop working to aid them and thus stop \\(otherwise\\) contributing to society and paying taxes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal consumption of heroin without any satisfactory hygiene conditions [supports](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/why-are-heroin-users-special-risk-contracting-hivaids-hepatitis-b-c) the development of HIV.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The effects of smoking are slow and not always visible; this means people are not as aware of them.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Marijuana use in the Netherlands has [not increased](https://www.opensocietyfoundations.org/voices/safe-and-effective-drug-policy-look-dutch) following decriminalisation; in fact, cannabis consumption is lower compared to countries with stricter legislation such as the UK.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The climb out of poverty is not helped by wasting resources on ingesting toxic materials.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs relate with [lower social skills](https://www.gatewayfoundation.org/substance-abuse-treatment-programs/effects-of-drug-abuse/) and antisocial behavior.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Professional addiction treatment is usually [expensive](https://www.addictioncenter.com/rehab-questions/cost-of-drug-and-alcohol-treatment/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Children of addicts may be raised in an environment which makes it [likelier for them](https://www.samhsa.gov/data/sites/default/files/report_3223/ShortReport-3223.html) to consume and become addicts in the future.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Opiates, such as heroin, are very detrimental to a persons health. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The anxiety induced by the threat of arrest can be a cause for the violent paranoia episodes some users experience while under the influence emotion enhancing substances.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is because the US prison system is [privately owned.](https://smartasset.com/mortgage/the-economics-of-the-american-prison-system) Incentive structures mean that running prisons can only be profitable with high rates of incarceration.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization does not treat addicts, treatment and prevention of the addiction do. Both of which can be done with drugs remaining illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Having any positive impacts at all is not to be conflated with being a net positive, or fully positive.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'True freedom of choice means that individuals must face the consequences of their actions, whether they are good or bad. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Banning drugs is akin to what happens in the film [Minority Report](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Minority_Report_\\(film\\)): it's arresting people for what they might do under the influence. We could as soon prosecute people for being out of work, drinking, gambling or adultery."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Someone experiencing elevated stress levels isn't a good enough justification to limit other people's freedom by force. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under prohibition, anything related to drugs use \\(like paraphernalia\\) would both be evidence of a crime and likely to be confiscated if found by police â€” this disincentive carrying anything other than the bare necessities to drug use.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Research suggests that [two-thirds](https://www.verywell.com/domestic-abuse-and-alcohol-62643) of incidents of domestic violence happen while the perpetrator is under the influence of alcohol.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug cartels destabilize Latin America. With legalization they would disappear and Latin America would gain stability.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drug legalisation will make it easier to carry out [sexual assaults](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug-facilitated_sexual_assault).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Taking drugs can be a pleasurable experience.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Lots of drug addicts don't want to use drugs, but they can't just simply choose to stop using drugs, because they have an addiction."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People who want to use drugs are largely already able to get access to them, but can have no assurance about their safety or quality. Government regulations could resolve this problem. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Removing some of these constraints through the legalisation of drugs could make studies more successful.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A higher number of drugs users will create more work for the accident and emergency paramedic services that have to deal with people who have overdosed due to improper usage.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar compound will always exist.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization will facilitate access to drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Tracing a car owner by his license plate after causing a severe accident with people killed does not undo the accident either. But it creates a moral barrier for people, so they think twice before doing such a hit and run. Same goes for traceable drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It can be argued that the terms 'recreational' and 'medicinal' are interchangeable. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The human right to personal autonomy](http://www.corteidh.or.cr/tablas/r26750.pdf) should include the freedom to take drugs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'People in poor health or overdosing on drugs are often not taken to receive medical attention for fear of criminal prosecution.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The Controlled Substances Act](https://www.dea.gov/druginfo/ds.shtml), prohibits Schedule 1 substances \\(such as Cannabis\\), which forces patients to either break the law or use more harmful/addictive substances that are inferior medicine. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The correlation between drug use and crime is fuelled at least partly by prohibition.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[New research](https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/full/10.1177/0269881118806297) on PTSD has shown that MDMA-assisted psychotherapy is an extremely effective treatment.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's important to have a standardized quantity of an active substance of controlled quality to prevent overdosing unwanted effects. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If a government wanted to put money into harm reduction, it could do so without legalising drugs in order to avoid the costs of enforcing a drug prohibition. It could instead cut other government programs.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many [deaths](http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-24581947) attributed to ecstasy \\(or MDMA\\) use are actually caused by other, unwanted ingredients.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Opiates have a [rich history](https://www.history.com/topics/crime/history-of-heroin-morphine-and-opiates) of recreational use, with the Ancient Sumerians calling it "The Joy Plant".'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Colorado has seen a "[slight increase](https://www.colorado.gov/pacific/cdphe/marijuana-use-2017)" in the number of adult marijuana users in the period 2014-2017 following legalisation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs other than alcohol were legalized, alcohol sales would plummet, and a lot of jobs in the alcohol industry would disappear.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Once you replace the dealers and kingpins of the neighborhoods whose flashy lifestyle would look appealing to naive kids, drugs would lose some of their appeal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Alcohol](https://theconversation.com/alcohol-leads-to-more-violence-than-other-drugs-but-youd-never-know-from-the-headlines-72281) is responsible for more violence and harm than any other drug.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing something means including it the current system of business oversight and regulation as other legal activities. This means documenting purchases and monetary transactions, as well as filing and paying taxes. This means more control over where drugs come from and money goes, rather than would be the case under prohibition or decriminalization.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The argument that illicit drugs can lead to addiction and should therefore be banned is a double standard, as various legal activities and substances are equally or even more addictive. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
